    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What are vegan gummy bears made of?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Vegan gummy bears use plant-based gelling agents — primarily pectin (from citrus peel or apple pomace), agar-agar (from seaweed), or tapioca starch — instead of animal-derived gelatin. They are typically sweetened with organic cane sugar, fruit juice, allulose, or stevia, and colored with fruit and vegetable concentrates rather than synthetic dyes or carmine (an insect-derived red pigment).' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Do vegan gummy bears taste like regular gummy bears?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes, modern vegan gummy bears are very close to gelatin-based gummy bears in flavor. The main difference is texture: pectin gummies are slightly softer with a less rubbery chew. Brands like Lovely Candy Co have developed formulations that closely replicate the traditional gelatin gummy bear texture. In blind taste tests, most consumers cannot reliably distinguish premium vegan gummy bears from conventional ones.' },
    },
