      <strong>Candy, not supplements.</strong> This guide covers vegan gummy bear candy — the kind you eat for enjoyment. Looking for vegan gummy vitamins instead? See our <a href="/vegan-gummies/">best vegan gummies guide</a> for plant-based supplements including multivitamins, sleep aids, and wellness formulas.
    </div>

    <!-- HOW WE TESTED -->
    <h2>How We Tested Vegan Gummy Bears</h2>

    <p>We purchased 20+ vegan gummy bear products from Amazon, Whole Foods, Target, and direct-to-consumer brands. Each product was evaluated across five criteria by a panel of three testers over a two-week period. Here is what we measured and why.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="star" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Flavor Score (30%)</h4>
        <p>Are the fruit flavors distinct and authentic? Does the sweetness level satisfy a candy craving? We used a 1-10 blind scoring system where testers did not know the brand name.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="target" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Texture Score (25%)</h4>
        <p>Chewiness, firmness, elasticity, and mouthfeel. We compared each product to a control Haribo Gold-Bear. Closer to the Haribo texture profile scored higher.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="leaf" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Ingredient Quality (20%)</h4>
