    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-sec">
      <h2>Vegan Gummy Bears — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What are vegan gummy bears made of?</summary><p>Vegan gummy bears use plant-based gelling agents — primarily pectin (from citrus peel or apple pomace), agar-agar (from seaweed), or tapioca starch — instead of animal-derived gelatin. They are sweetened with organic cane sugar, fruit juice, allulose, or stevia.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Do vegan gummy bears taste like regular gummy bears?</summary><p>Yes, modern vegan gummy bears are very close in flavor. The main difference is texture: pectin gummies are slightly softer. Brands like Lovely Candy Co have formulations that closely replicate gelatin texture. Most consumers cannot distinguish them in blind tests.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are all gummy bears with pectin vegan?</summary><p>Not necessarily. A gummy bear can use pectin but still contain beeswax, carmine, or shellac. Always check the full ingredient list or look for a Certified Vegan logo.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What is the best low-sugar vegan gummy bear?</summary><p>SmartSweets at 3g sugar per bag. Project 7 is a close second at 4g with bolder flavors and a lower price.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are Haribo gummy bears vegan?</summary><p>No. Haribo Gold-Bears contain pork-derived gelatin and beeswax. They do not offer a vegan line in the US.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are vegan gummy bears healthier than regular gummy bears?</summary><p>It depends on the brand. SmartSweets (3g sugar) is significantly healthier than Haribo (34g sugar). But some vegan bears have comparable sugar — they are just gelatin-free, not necessarily low-sugar.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Where can I buy vegan gummy bears?</summary><p>Amazon (widest selection), Whole Foods, Target, Walmart, Trader Joe's, and Sprouts. Amazon Subscribe & Save offers the best multi-pack pricing.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Can kids eat vegan gummy bears?</summary><p>Yes. Surf Sweets and YumEarth are especially popular with parents — USDA Organic, allergen-free, and colored with real fruit and vegetable juices. Always check for individual allergen concerns.</p></details>
    </section>

